t years. Its scope has expanded and it has become more open and pluralistic in its methodology. This compendium assembles 52 essays by scholars from around the world. It illustrates the diversity of methodological approaches and thematic breadth of new international historiography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aEuropexHistory. 0aHistory, Moderny19th century. 0aHistory, Moderny20th century. 4aEuropäische Geschichte. 4aInternationale Geschichte. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aEuropean history.  aInternational history.1 aBachem-Rehm, Michaela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBachem-Rehm, Michaela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBajohr, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBajon, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarthel, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlasius, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBossuat, Gérard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClemens, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCobet, Justus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConze, Eckart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoering-Manteuffel, Anselm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDülffer, Jost, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelbrecht, Jörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrie, Ewald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFößel, Amalie, econtributo